<p>Outstanding value comes from lesser-known Loire appellations like <strong>Quincy and Reuilly</strong>, offering Sancerre-quality at half the price. On labels, seek <strong>"Sur Lie"</strong> indicating extended yeast contact for added texture, <strong>"Vieilles Vignes"</strong> for old-vine concentration, and specific vineyard designations showing producer commitment to terroir.</p>

<p>For New Zealand wines, <strong>"Central Otago"</strong> and <strong>"Hawke's Bay"</strong> offer alternatives to mainstream Marlborough with unique mineral profiles.</p>

